<br>
Friday heralded the worst paperwork snafu in Santa Carla history. Do to various errors in clerical and paperwork, serious permanent damage has been done to a number of longstanding properties in the county, and a multitude of businesses were inconvenienced.<br>
<br>
Somehow three properties, one the historic #### Villa in the Santa Carla hills, were razed. Paperwork showed that all three properties had been sited for various violations, and declared unsuitable for habitation. Crews assigned to the demolitions were all confused and upset by the situation. No one could be found for comment. A trailer park in Davenport and an office building downtown were the other two properties destroyed. The City has released a statement of &quot;no statement&quot; regarding the situation. All the paperwork was apparently completely in order and signed off by all the appropriate officials. The Santa Carla Investment Union is giving short term no-interest loans to the families displaced by the loss of their homes in the trailer park. Luckily the damage to the building downtown was mostly cosmetic, demolitions were halted before structural integrity was lost in the building. The #### Villa will be sadly missed. Like the old Cooper House, all that remains are a few old vintage photos.<br>
<br>
In a similar but unrelated situation 10 downtown clubs and eating establishments were closed down by the Health Department. &quot;There appears to have been some sort of computer virus&quot;, stated Paul Deeman, Supervisor. All 10 establishments came up for inspection on the same day and once their reports were filed, all were slated for shut down due to multiple violations. The Underground, The Silver Saloon, and The Black Swan, all brand new and popular venues were closed Friday nite, as well as Club Vinyl, Little Shanghai, Shogun, El Palomar, and others. Quick and firm action on the parts of owners and the general public had the establishments back in business by this morning. &quot;It was obvious to us upon review, that some error had occured, and we moved quickly to rectify the situation. We are here for the good of the public and the consumer, not to inconvenience reliable establishments.&quot; said Mr. Deeman. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm18.showPrevMessage?topicID=19.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm18.showNextMessage?topicID=19.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/prefabs/ez/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm18.threadControl?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm18.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click 